	(1599,2022,'biographical_info','I trained as a bander on Appledore and then ran a banding station on nearby Star Island (also on the Isles of Shoals) for my master’s thesis. I compared the birds captured and determined there was a difference between the islands based on habitat. Birds that prefer shrubland and open habitat were more common on Star and those that typically use large forested areas were more common on Appledore. It was such a terrific experience that I returned to Appledore when it was completed and have been banding here ever since.'),
