	(1670,2033,'biographical_info','I am a retired high school English and journalism teacher who is now president of North Shore Audubon Society on Long Island.  I volunteer for many educational activities for fourth grade students to learn about science using birds and in the planning and planting of native plant gardens in public places.  I just started helping a bird bander, Harvey Farber, on the south shore of Long Island during migrations.  I was a reporter for a local newspaper for 3 years.'),
