	(1946,1,'2016-05-03 13:53:35','2016-05-03 13:53:35','The Appledore Island Migration Station (AIMS) is located on Appledore Island in the Gulf of Maine. \r\nAppledore Island is also home to the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.shoalsmarinelaboratory.org/\">Shoals Marine Lab</a> (SML), which is run cooperatively by Cornell University and the University of New Hampshire and which hosts the banding station.\r\nThe AIMS banding station has been in operation on Appledore since 19##. Each spring and fall migration season, AIMS staff run the banding station dawn to dusk, seven days a week, weather permitting.\r\nAIMS is staffed entirely by volunteers and students.\r\n\r\nBird Banding Ethics:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The AIMS banding station has been <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://burtonux.com/aims/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/AIMS-NABC-STATION-SIGN.docx\">AIMS NABC STATION SIGN</a>certified by the North American Banding Council</a> (NABC)</li>\r\n	<li>Four of the banders at the station are certified by NABC at the Trainer level</li>\r\n	<li>AIMS abides by the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.nabanding.net/banders-code-of-ethics/\">NABC Bander\'s Code of Ethics</a> in all its operations.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n ','Bird Banding at AIMS','','trash','closed','closed','','bird-banding-at-aims__trashed','','','2016-05-06 23:11:59','2016-05-06 23:11:59','',0,'http://burtonux.com/aims/?post_type=aims_info&#038;p=1946',0,'aims_info','',0),
