	(1948,1,'2016-05-04 12:51:14','2016-05-04 12:51:14','Volunteering at the banding station on Appledore can be grueling but it has many rewards. While the days are long and the conditions can be challenging at times, many of our volunteers have been coming season after season for many years.\r\n\r\nVolunteers at Appledore are carefully trained in a number of skills, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Safe handling of bird</li>\r\n	<li>Data recording</li>\r\n	<li>Weighing and releasing birds</li>\r\n	<li>Net extraction</li>\r\n	<li>Bird identification</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nInterested potential volunteers without previous bird banding experience are encouraged to take the week-long training course, Dangle Tangle and Drudge, offered by bander David Holmes in the fall.\r\n\r\n[Info about Dangle Tangle]','Volunteer Info','','inherit','closed','closed','','1836-revision-v1','','','2016-05-04 12:51:14','2016-05-04 12:51:14','',1836,'http://burtonux.com/aims/2016/05/04/1836-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(1949,1,'2016-05-04 12:58:49','2016-05-04 12:58:49','Volunteering at the banding station on Appledore can be grueling but it has many rewards. While the days are long and the conditions can be challenging at times, many of our volunteers have been coming season after season for many years.\r\n\r\nVolunteers at Appledore are carefully trained in a number of skills, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Safe handling of birds</li>\r\n	<li>Data recording</li>\r\n	<li>Weighing and releasing birds</li>\r\n	<li>Net extraction</li>\r\n	<li>Bird identification</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nInterested potential volunteers without previous bird banding experience are encouraged to take the week-long training course, Dangle Tangle and Drudge, offered by bander David Holmes in the fall.\r\n\r\n<h2>Dangle, Tangle and Drudge<h2>\r\n\r\nThis non-credit course is intended to give the participants beginning levels of a variety of mist netting skills with the goal of making them capable of helping with the AIMS banding project (or others) in subsequent years.  In this course, we will learn about handling nets, birds, and birds in nets.  We will also cover the basic processing techniques of identification, aging, sexing, measuring, and weighing.  There will be as much hands-on experience as the birds and your skills will allow.\r\nThe course is about 6 days long and generally takes place in early September. There is a cost of $90 per day for the course plus the boat fee ($60). This cost covers your room and board while staying on the island &mdash; instructors are not paid. \r\n','Volunteer Info','','inherit','closed','closed','','1836-revision-v1','','','2016-05-04 12:58:49','2016-05-04 12:58:49','',1836,'http://burtonux.com/aims/2016/05/04/1836-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
