	(1955,1,'2016-05-04 13:08:21','2016-05-04 13:08:21','Volunteering at the banding station on Appledore can be grueling but it has many rewards. While the days are long and the conditions can be challenging at times, many of our volunteers have been coming season after season for many years.\r\n\r\nVolunteers at Appledore are carefully trained in a number of skills, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Safe handling of birds</li>\r\n	<li>Data recording</li>\r\n	<li>Weighing and releasing birds</li>\r\n	<li>Net extraction</li>\r\n	<li>Bird identification</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Dangle, Tangle and Drudge</h2>\r\n<p>Interested potential volunteers without previous bird banding experience are encouraged to take the week-long training course, Dangle Tangle and Drudge, offered by bander David Holmes in the fall.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This non-credit course is intended to give the participants beginning levels of a variety of mist netting skills with the goal of making them capable of helping with the AIMS banding project (or others) in subsequent seasons. In this course, you will learn about handling nets, birds, and birds in nets. You will also be exposed to the basic processing techniques of identification, aging, sexing, measuring, and weighing. There will be as much hands-on experience as possible.</p>\r\n<p>The course lasts approximately 6 days and generally takes place in early September. The current price for the course is $600. This cost covers your room and board while staying on the island and your boat fees. Instructors are not paid.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n','Volunteer Info','','inherit','closed','closed','','1836-revision-v1','','','2016-05-04 13:08:21','2016-05-04 13:08:21','',1836,'http://burtonux.com/aims/2016/05/04/1836-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
